#EXCEPTION HANDLING

1) What is Exception?
Abnormal Behaviour in programs

Abnormal events which stops the program abruptly.             

100% Object Oriented Programming

Primitive data types: int,float

#EXCEPTION: whenever Exception occurs, the corresponding exception object will be thrown

*Direct subclasses of Throwable class: Error,Exception

Object class->Throwable class->exception


#ERROR
*Error is a subclass of Throwable that indicates serious problems 
that a reasonable application should not try to catch.

*The class Exception and its subclasses are a form of Throwable 
that indicates conditions that a reasonable application might want to catch

#EXCEPTION
checked exception--->Compile Time Exception
unchecked exception--->RuntimeException

A throwable contains a snapshot of the execution stack of its thread at the time it was created.
It can also contain a message string thst gives more information about the error.

1) Stack-Line no
2) Exception Name
3) Message String


#final
*Access Modifier
*final class - cannot be extended
*final method - cannot be overridden
*final variable - value cannot be changed

#finlize()
*To remove an object from the memory,garbage collector will call 